news_header: Chinese companies are advancing in artificial intelligence, with Alibaba releasing a new version of its Qwen AI, claiming it outperforms US counterparts.
news_text: In response to the Deepsee competition, several Chinese companies have released new artificial intelligence technologies. Alibaba recently launched its Qwen AI, claiming it surpasses US AI models like OpenAI's GPT-4o and Meta's Llama-3.1 in various tasks, particularly in image and video analysis. However, independent evaluations of Qwen's performance are still pending. The release timing coincides with the Chinese New Year, highlighting the competitive landscape in AI development in China, especially following Deepsee's recent launch. Other companies like Bytedance and Moonshot AI have also introduced their AI models.
